reviewText: Very interesting story.  Scenery is breathtaking.
Got this just to see more of Craig Olejnik after becoming familiar with him on "The Listener."  Love that man!
I'm a fan of Craig Olejnik so I have enjoyed this movie. Have watched it twice

Excellent movie!  Craig Olejnik does a brilliant job in the title role. The actor is the star of "The Listener" Canadian TV series and it's nice to see him as a different character.  He is one of my favorite actors.
Timekeeper  was just so not what i thought it was about  to my great delight this low budget one is very surprising indeed.

I'm from Spain and I was looking for this movie for a long time, and I was not disappointed...I love it, very good movie, very good actors, Craig Olejnik was excellent and the soundtrack is amazing! Just perfect.

excellent story... excellent acting. The horrors of expansionism. across Canada. How men can harm men and kill a landscape. Very good

Having seen a trailer for this film it piqued my interest and one of the lead actors
appears in the 'Jesse Stone' series. I was not disappointed and recommend it
highly.

This was a well written story of a young man's growning pains. It shows how a man with strong ethics can sometimes stand strong against the unethical people during hard times in the 1930's. The background scene is breath-taking. I am happy that I purchased this film, and suggest you do the same.
